WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.960
You know, people love RStudio, they love the IDE, they love our pro products, and it's

00:00:07.960 --> 00:00:13.880
been really tough working through the rebrand of RStudio, worrying that R users would get

00:00:13.880 --> 00:00:17.879
the message that, like, we don't believe in R anymore.

00:00:17.879 --> 00:00:19.559
And that's absolutely not the case.

00:00:19.559 --> 00:00:24.799
Like, Posit! is not about, like, pivoting from R to Python, it's about broadening and

00:00:24.799 --> 00:00:28.799
embracing the Python community as well as the R community.

00:00:28.799 --> 00:00:35.160
So I think that's my big message for the R community, is, like, we still 100% believe

00:00:35.160 --> 00:00:42.040
in R, I think it is just a fantastic environment for doing interactive data science, and we're

00:00:42.040 --> 00:00:44.160
going to continue to invest in it.

00:00:44.160 --> 00:00:49.959
But what I hope we can bring to the Python ecosystem is some of the sort of, like, beautiful

00:00:49.959 --> 00:00:55.360
end-to-end orchestration that we've provided the R community, where things just work.

00:00:55.799 --> 00:01:00.680
And I think that is, you know, very, you know, broadly what we want with all of our open

00:01:00.680 --> 00:01:06.919
source products, with all of our pro products, that you try something and it just works first

00:01:06.919 --> 00:01:10.239
time, and that it's just such a joyful experience.

